FBIS3-37260 "drsov031__a94019" FBIS-SOV-94-031 Document Type:Daily Report 15 February 1994 ANNEX Armenia Comments on Karabakh `Genocide' NC1102135394 Yerevan ARAGIL ELECTRONIC NEWS BULLETIN in English 0948 GMT 11 Feb 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY NC1102135394 Yerevan ARAGIL ELECTRONIC NEWS BULLETIN Language: English Article Type:BFN [Quotation marks as received] [Text] London ("AZG" daily), 11/02/94--"The war which is now carried between the Mountainous Karabakh and Azerbaijan may possibly grow soon into a war between Armenia and Azerbaijan, the president of the Republic of Armenia declared today during the meeting with journalists in the Carlton hotel of London. This was probably the first time when the RA [Republic of Armenia] president officially declared that Armenia will interfere with the Karabakh conflict if a danger of genocide or moving the population of Karabakh appears. In this case, Levon Ter-Petrosyan stressed, Armenia will participate in the conflict no regard who will be in power by that time. This will depend on the will of the people. Our people will not allow a new genocide", the president noted.
